derivation: or שׁוּבָאֵל; from H7617 (שָׁבָה) (abbreviated form) or H7725 (שׁוּב) and H410 (אֵל); captive (or returned) of God;
outline:
Shebuel or Shubael = "captive of God"
  1. son of Gershom and grandson of Moses
  2. one of the 14 sons of Heman the musician
strongs_def: Shebuel or Shubael, the name of two Israelites
